        <briefdescription>
<para>Interface-level frame encryption security key material. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Currently native L2 only supports a single secKeySource, see section 9.5, table 9-9, in combination with secKeyMode zero (implicit key mode), see section 9.4.2.3, table 9-7.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="warning"><para>This is no longer in accordance with the 2015+ versions of the standard and needs to be extended in the future for full security procedure compliance. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
